<TITLE> Chittagong shaken by mild quake </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 14 (bdnews24.com)Residents in the Chittagong area were shaken by a mild quake late Tuesday night. The met office's seismic observation centre said the quake hit at 10.57pm, with its epicentre some 316 km southeast of Dhaka on the Bangladesh-Myanmar border. A resident of Chakuria Upazila in Cox's Bazar, Habibul Hossain, told bdnews24.com: "We felt the quake. The walls here were shaking." NGO worker Subrata Dhar said he felt "a moderate jolt for a few seconds" in Roomghata, Chittagong city. There were also reports of tremors at Kutubdia Island. Dhaka University's earth observatory director Prof Syed Humayun Aktar said the quake was a result of the Sitakunda-Teknaf-Myanmar subduction fault, which is currently active.
